.IX Title "wk2txt 1"
.TH wk2txt 1 "2009-01-09" "0.1.0" "wk2txt"
.SH "NAME"
wk2txt \- A Website to Text Converter
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
\&\fBwk2txt\fR \fIoptions\fR
.PP
Options:
  \-\-input \s-1URL\s0               convert \fI\s-1URL\s0\fR to text
  \-\-urlfile file            convert URLs in \fIfile\fR to text
  \-\-output directory        save output in directory \fIdirectory\fR
  \-\-xml                     dump in \s-1XML\s0 format
  \-\-timeout inverval        timeout after \fIinterval\fR seconds (\s-1NOT\s0 \s-1IMPLEMENTED\s0)
  \-\-debug                   print diagnostic information
  \-\-help                    print help on options
  \-\-version                 print version number
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
wk2txt is a command line tool based on the WebKit Engine to get the text content 
of a websites as seen by current webbrowsers which includes the evaluation of 
javascript code present in many modern webpages.
.PP
wk2txt can process a whole list of URLs, which can be built by using the 
\&\f(CW\*(C`\-\-input\*(C'\fR option multiple times or by passing the filename of a list of URLs to
the \f(CW\*(C`\-\-urlfile\*(C'\fR. This file is expected to have 1 \s-1URL\s0 per line.
.PP
The contents of the webpages is written to one file per webpage. The files are
stored in the directory specified by the \f(CW\*(C`\-\-output\*(C'\fR option. The filename is 
derived from the \s-1URL\s0, it is the \s-1SHA1\s0 hash code for the \s-1URL\s0.
.PP
By default, wk2txt dumps the contents and the meta data of the webpage in plain
text format. If the \f(CW\*(C`\-\-xml\*(C'\fR option is used, content and meta data is dumped in
\&\s-1XML\s0 format.
